articles.title: Asia markets edge lower ahead of key China data - CNBC
articles.description: China's third quarter GDP, September retail sales came in stronger than expected and urban unemployment fell to its lowest level in almost two years last month.
articles.content:
Asia markets were mixed in choppy afternoon trading on Wednesday after economic data from China showed stronger-than-expected growth.
